#USMarketUpdate#PerformanceSummaryU.S. stocks higher at close of trade; Dow Jones Industrial Average up 1.12%Investing.comâ€“U.S. stocks were higher after the close on Tuesday  as gains in the Industrials  Basic Materials and Utilities sectors led shares higher.At the close in NYSE  the Dow Jones Industrial Average added 1.12%  while the S&P 500 index climbed 1.14%  and the NASDAQ Composite index gained 0.90%.The top performers on the S&P 500 were Carnival Corporation (NYSE:CCL) which rose 11.28% to 8.09  Lockheed Martin Corporation (NYSE:LMT) which was up 8.69% to settle at 431.84 and Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd (NYSE:NCLH) which gained 8.57% to close at 14.31.The worst performerswere Moderna Inc (NASDAQ:MRNA) which was down 3.71% to 134.09 in late trade  Hasbro Inc (NASDAQ:HAS) which lost 2.88% to settle at 65.76 and DexCom Inc (NASDAQ:DXCM) which was down 2.81% to 96.93 at the close.Rising stocks outnumbered declining ones on the New York Stock Exchange by 2299 to 820 and 105 ended unchanged; on the Nasdaq Stock Exchange  2446 rose and 1303 declined  while 247 ended unchanged.The CBOE Volatility Index  which measures the implied volatility of S&P 500 options  was down 2.77% to 30.50.Gold Futures for December delivery was down 0.43% or 7.20 to $1 656.80 a troy ounce. Elsewhere in commodities trading Crude oil for delivery in December fell 2.33% or 1.97 to hit $82.56 a barrel while the December Brent oil contract fell 1.44% or 1.32 to trade at $90.30 a barrel.The US Dollar Index Futures was down 0.02% at 111.88.https://www.investing.com/news/stock-market-news/us-stocks-higher-at-close-of-trade-dow-jones-industrial-average-up-112-2915290
